"{\n  \"text\": \"Hey everybody, Scotty here with Scotty's Fermented Foods. I want to do a quick video about my chickens and the wonders that they do, not just in giving me delicious eggs, but also in working my land, uh, or you know, in this case my backyard. Uh this is my compost curing area, and I let the chickens on here about every third day, and they pluck out a lot of the grubs and worms and other things in there, and they just peck and scratch and move it all around. And they're not only getting uh great protein to make great eggs, but they're also stirring my compost pile. And this is the curing area, so this is all cooled down. It just needs a little bit of mixing, and that's what they're doing. They're gonna scratch and peck and mix the top two layers of this, and that's gonna be a great action in terms of uh just spreading bacteria, spreading material, getting it broken down a little bit further, getting it mixed up, getting it aerated, and they just do a great job on this. And this is one of the most important parts of regenerative agriculture is getting animals to work for it.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" Hey everybody, Scotty here with Scotty's Fermented Foods.\",\n      \"start\": 0.32,\n      \"end\": 3.04,\n      \"duration\": 2.72,\n      \"confidence\": 0.988,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" He\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.48,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.968\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"y\",\n          \"start\": 0.48,\n          \"end\": 0.56,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \" ever\",\n          \"start\": 0.64,\n          \"end\": 0.72,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"yb\",\n          \"start\": 0.72,\n          \"end\": 0.8,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidenc